node.text: From reefs to ridges, explore the beauty of the Philippines through the eyes of the locals. While 2020 has been a year of change for travel, the Philippines is excited to invite local visitors to explore the beautiful islands. The #BDTeam had the pleasure of working with @tourism_phl to highlight beautiful places around the Philippines. The opportunities for exploration are endless-from the Hundred Island National Park in Pangasinan to exploring the Suba and Culili Sand Dunes in Ilocos Norte.

node.text:
With an incredibly rich history, being an “Egyptian” can have many facets especially when it comes to creativity. Today, we’re sharing a unique story dedicated to any creative who intends to carve their own path no matter the circumstances. 

“It’s proof that the end product most of the time doesn’t pan out the way you expect it. And its by having expectations that you hinder your potential.” - @matiasderada

Watch this beautiful film on Beautiful Destinations Youtube channel. 🇪🇬

🎥 @matiasderada #BDTeam

Bristol Bay, one of Alaska’s most treasured natural wonders, is under threat. @world_wildlife 

It’s home to an irreplaceable ecosystem and one of the last salmon strongholds. Not only that, its iconic wildlife has sprung up a sustainable tourism industry which effects thousands of Alaskan livelihoods.

All of this is under threat if the Pebble Mine moves forward. The recent approval of the environmental impact statement has made it clear that our voices need to be heard. 

Nature and people can’t live without fresh water, and Bristol Bay is the lifeblood that sustains every species calling the region home. 

On a recent trip to Alaska, the #BDTeam and WWF Ambassador, @jeremyjauncey, learned firsthand about the conservation community’s fight against Pebble Mine.

node.text: As New York City starts to open back up, we wanted to take a moment to reflect on the efforts of heroes in the hospitality industry who have been helping our frontline workers. @fsnewyork was the first hotel in New York City to open its door to our frontline workers and provide them with a safe haven to stay during such an uncertain time. They quickly transformed the hotel into a near medical-grade facility. Over 300 medical workers called @fsnewyork home during this time as they were provided rooms free of charge. This allowed them to keep their own families safe as they focused on their work and taking care of patients. ❤️ (🎥: @loganlambert 📸: @loganstrongarms 📍: Four Seasons Hotel New York)

A volunteer taking care of a turtle at the @ogasawara_marine_centre, an environmental conservation organization that aims to protect green turtles and other creatures in Ogasawara, Japan. 🐢

The "Turtle Center" takes in and rehabilitates ill or injured sea turtles, and helps raise young turtles from eggs to their release into the wild. It's nestled in the Ogasawara Islands, a World Natural Heritage Site and an archipelago of over 30 subtropical and tropical islands located south of Tokyo. 🇯🇵

Have you ever spent time volunteering during your travels? 💙

📽 @ogasawara_marine_centre 
📍 Ogasawara Islands, Tokyo
🎶 Makana - Glow Of The Moon

Big mood via @elias_schwaerzler when we finally wake up to the weekend. 🙌🏼 Waking up bright and early in the Silvretta-Stausee in Austria is a great way to jumpstart the morning. ☀️

The Silvretta-Stausee is a reservoir situated at the highest point of the Silvretta High-Alpine Road. It features three dams and a beautiful circular hike surrounding the reservoir that's commonly used for cycling, hiking, and bird watching. It's a great place to spend quality time with friends and family! 🇦🇹

How did your week go and how do you plan to spend the weekend? 🚴

📽 @elias_schwaerzler

Our current mood is @kamalugoo diving into the most beautiful sunset view in Hawaii. 🙌🏼 Hawaiian sunsets, with their stunning vibrant colors, are spectacular, to say the least. 🔥

Hawaii's geography as well as the humidity and volcanic dust high in the atmosphere aids in intensifying its sunsets' colors. Another reason is that the sun sinks into the Pacific Ocean, which is distant from any landmass that could disturb the atmosphere or break the horizon line. The angle of the sunset is as great as it can get. 😍

Where have you seen the most beautiful sunsets? ⛅️

📽 @kamalugoo
📍 Hawaii

Marveling at @amr.a.salah's footage of the ancient temple complex of Abu Simbel, built approximately between 1264-244 BCE. 😮🇪🇬

The Abu Simbel Temple comprises two individual temples, both rock-cut structures built during the reign of King Ramses II. One temple is dedicated to King Ramses II and the second temple is dedicated to his wife Queen Nefertari. The carvings and artwork that decorate the temples are extremely delicate, having lived through thousands of years.

Do you enjoy learning about history? What are other interesting facts and trivia about Egypt? 📜

📽 @amr.a.salah 
📍 Abu Simbel, Egypt
🎶 Various Artists, Derek Fiechter - Pharaoh Ramses II

A dust devil spotted by @rodrigoviverosphoto in Alto Las Vizcachas, Chile. 🇨🇱 Have you ever seen one in person? 😮

Also known as sand devils, dust devils are an interesting phenomena that usually show up under hot, clear-sky conditions with light winds. They're relatively small and brief whirlwinds that occur when a land surface heats rapidly, with much cooler air above it. The hot air then stretches and causes a spinning motion, similar to a tornado.🌪

📽 @rodrigoviverosphoto
📍 Alto Las Vizcachas, Chile

We're marveling at @mitchellpettigrew's stunning photographs of Queensland, a paradise in Australia that offers something for all kinds of travelers. 😍

If you're wondering what the best things to do here are, bookmark this and tag your travel crew! 🇦🇺

𝟭𝟬 𝗧𝗵𝗶𝗻𝗴𝘀 𝗧𝗼 𝗗𝗼 𝗶𝗻 𝗤𝘂𝗲𝗲𝗻𝘀𝗹𝗮𝗻𝗱
1. Soak up the sun in the Gold Coast's beaches, like the popular Surfers Paradise.
2. Go snorkeling in the Great Barrier Reef.
3. Learn about nature, culture, and history at the Daintree Rainforest.
4. Discover Cairns' café scene and beach markets.
5. Have fun at theme parks like Dreamworld and Warner Bros. Movie World. 
6. Relish in fresh seafood and local produce at the Sunshine Coast.
7. Have a drink at the rooftop bars in Brisbane.
8. Explore weekend markets and vintage shops at West End.
9. Encounter wildlife at animal sanctuaries.
10. Climb the iconic landmark of the Storey Bridge.

Have you been to Queensland yet? What else is missing from this list? 🤔

📸 @mitchellpettigrew
📍 Queensland, Australia

Walking past @shanef3d's epic display of Zara in SoHo, New York that will truly make you stop and stare. Isn't this the coolest digital art of a storefront you've ever seen? 😮

SoHo, an acronym for South of Houston Street, is a popular neighborhood tucked in Lower Manhattan in New York City. It features art galleries, luxury boutiques, and independent-designer outposts, as well as a buzzing nightlife scene. If you love shopping and living a cosmopolitan lifestyle, make your way down to this artsy neighborhood. 🛍

📽 @shanef3d
📍 SoHo, New York, USA
